01:05.266 --> 01:07.636
Shaver's remorse.

01:07.638 --> 01:10.638
I kind of got used to all that extra fur.

01:10.640 --> 01:11.974
Ah, you don't need it anymore, Hank.

01:14.148 --> 01:15.381
Uh, it's $30 now.

01:15.383 --> 01:17.617
$30? Franco, it was $10 a few weeks ago.

01:17.619 --> 01:19.119
It was $10 a few hours ago.

01:19.121 --> 01:20.755
All right.

01:22.793 --> 01:24.495
Ooh, nice haircut, doctor.

01:24.497 --> 01:25.931
How do I look?

01:25.933 --> 01:27.833
Like a victim of highway robbery.

01:27.835 --> 01:28.835
How much did you pay?

01:28.837 --> 01:30.271
More than usual, less than you.

01:30.273 --> 01:32.108
Well, Paige is worth every penny.

01:32.110 --> 01:33.843
You think she's with you for your hair?

01:33.845 --> 01:35.445
Well, she gets back today,

01:35.447 --> 01:37.348
and everything at her party
should be perfect...

01:37.350 --> 01:38.750
everything, especially me.

01:38.752 --> 01:40.018
Party? What party?

01:40.020 --> 01:41.420
The one I'm throwing her today.

01:41.422 --> 01:42.722
Ev, you throw her a party

01:42.724 --> 01:44.223
every time she gets back from a trip,

01:44.225 --> 01:45.524
and she takes a lot of trips.

01:45.526 --> 01:49.464
I know. I... I... I wanna
incentivize her to come home.

01:49.466 --> 01:50.866
It's my dangling carrot.

01:50.868 --> 01:53.536
And how big will today's carrot be?

01:53.538 --> 01:55.839
Today's carrot will be very exclusive...

01:55.841 --> 01:56.974
- Honestly.
- Okay.

01:56.976 --> 01:58.476
You, me, me...

01:58.478 --> 02:00.412
Remind me why we need a P.O. Box.

02:00.414 --> 02:02.014
Uh, you want our patients to know

02:02.016 --> 02:03.515
we're still crashing at Newberg's?

02:03.517 --> 02:04.884
Better than them thinking we run

02:04.886 --> 02:06.286
a mail-order medical practice.

02:06.288 --> 02:08.354
This is for me, me, me.

02:08.357 --> 02:11.358
Oh, this cool one's for you.
Just kidding. It's for me!

02:11.360 --> 02:12.426
Me...

02:12.428 --> 02:14.662
Me...

02:14.664 --> 02:16.864
Oh, check it out... it's a postcard.

02:16.866 --> 02:18.232
Who sent a postcard?

02:18.234 --> 02:20.334
Jill... From Uruguay.

02:20.336 --> 02:21.702
Jill sent you a postcard?

02:21.704 --> 02:23.170
No, she sent it to you.

02:23.172 --> 02:24.772
Then why are you reading it?

02:24.774 --> 02:26.140
It's a postcard.

02:26.142 --> 02:29.810
You want privacy, tell her
to spring for an envelope.

02:31.446 --> 02:33.048
I wonder what her "big news" is.

02:33.050 --> 02:34.316
Yeah.

02:34.318 --> 02:36.685
Me too.

02:36.687 --> 02:37.820
Me...

02:37.822 --> 02:40.190
You, and...

02:40.192 --> 02:42.193
"occupant".

02:42.195 --> 02:44.662
Looks like summer has arrived.

02:46.199 --> 02:48.500
Her name is Divya.

02:52.172 --> 02:53.740
Hi, Divya.

02:53.742 --> 02:55.709
Isn't it a bit early for lunch?

02:55.711 --> 02:57.911
I haven't worked up an appetite just yet.

03:06.556 --> 03:08.991
Divya, check those two drivers.

03:12.030 --> 03:13.763
Miss, wait. Are you hurt?

03:13.765 --> 03:15.832
I don't think so.
I hit the brakes just in time.

03:15.834 --> 03:17.634
Call 911. Tell them
we have a bus collision

03:17.636 --> 03:18.869
with possible injuries.

03:18.871 --> 03:20.204
Got it. Where are you going?

03:20.206 --> 03:21.238
In there.

03:24.644 --> 03:28.147
Excuse me. Just coming in.

03:28.149 --> 03:30.850
Hi. Hi.

03:30.852 --> 03:32.652
Everyone, please stay still.
I'm a doctor.

03:32.654 --> 03:34.788
I'm gonna make sure
you're all okay one at a time.

03:34.790 --> 03:36.484
All right, ambulances are en route.

03:36.486 --> 03:37.724
I ordered a few, just in case.

03:37.726 --> 03:39.159
Evan? Evan, what are you doing in here?

03:39.161 --> 03:41.061
When you come in,
we come in behind you, man.

03:41.063 --> 03:43.930
- We?
- Both drivers are okay...

03:43.932 --> 03:45.966
just a little shaken.

03:45.968 --> 03:48.535
The woman promised to call
if anything pops up.

03:48.537 --> 03:51.071
Divya, triage
from the other end of the bus.

03:51.073 --> 03:54.041
Anyone who can exit safely,
come up to this window, please.

03:54.043 --> 03:56.344
Ev, there are people outside
who can help you off-load.

03:56.346 --> 03:57.545
- Okay.
- Can I help?

03:57.547 --> 03:58.813
Do you know what happened?

03:58.815 --> 04:01.282
Yeah, about 250 grand worth
of midlife crisis

04:01.284 --> 04:03.585
came straight at me, and I had to swerve.

04:03.587 --> 04:04.987
Uh, what's the plan?

04:04.989 --> 04:06.221
The door is jammed. It won't open.

04:06.223 --> 04:07.990
Yeah, I saw. Can you pop another window?

04:07.992 --> 04:10.859
Yeah, I'll give it my best try.

04:10.861 --> 04:12.494
Aah! Aah!

04:12.496 --> 04:14.230
Okay, okay, stay still, sir.

04:14.232 --> 04:16.332
Stay still. Where's the pain?

04:16.334 --> 04:19.302
Oh! My left leg is killing me!

04:20.303 --> 04:21.837
Aah!

04:21.839 --> 04:24.774
Okay, okay. All right.

04:28.879 --> 04:31.013
- What's your name?
- Rob.

04:31.015 --> 04:33.015
Rob, you fractured your femur.

04:33.017 --> 04:36.018
- Ev, is everyone else out?
- Uh, just a couple more to go.

04:36.020 --> 04:38.754
Okay, good, good.
I need you over here now.

04:38.756 --> 04:40.255
Come here.

04:40.257 --> 04:42.357
Okay, Rob, this is my brother, Evan.

04:42.359 --> 04:43.925
He's gonna be your temporary splint.

04:43.927 --> 04:45.027
- What?
- What!?

04:45.029 --> 04:46.728
It's called a human-hare splint.

04:46.730 --> 04:48.097
Okay, now, sit down.

04:48.099 --> 04:51.400
Okay, good.

04:51.402 --> 04:52.801
That's it.

04:52.803 --> 04:55.104
Extend your left leg
till your foot hits this pillow.

04:55.106 --> 04:56.772
- Now grab his ankle...
- Okay.

04:56.774 --> 04:59.242
And extend your back
till you're lying on the floor.

04:59.244 --> 05:01.511
- What?
- Just lie down.

05:01.513 --> 05:03.079
Good. Now, use all your strength

05:03.081 --> 05:04.581
to keep his leg completely straight.

05:04.583 --> 05:05.915
But that's gonna really hu...

05:05.917 --> 05:06.916
- Now.
- Aah!

05:06.918 --> 05:09.652
Okay.

05:09.654 --> 05:12.288
Oh. Oh, my God.
Oh, that's so much better.

05:12.290 --> 05:13.823
Hank!

05:13.825 --> 05:16.092
Good. Now, just hold him
till I tell you to stop.

05:16.094 --> 05:17.260
Hank!

05:17.262 --> 05:20.163
We were helping the last passenger out.

05:20.165 --> 05:24.234
He just doubled over in pain
and then just collapsed.

05:30.908 --> 05:32.308
He got impaled
with a piece of broken glass.

05:32.310 --> 05:34.677
I had a bottle of iced tea in my lap.

05:34.679 --> 05:36.613
I didn't feel anything till just now.

05:36.615 --> 05:38.515
Your adrenaline was masking the pain.

05:38.517 --> 05:40.217
Helping the passengers out
probably opened the wound.

05:40.219 --> 05:42.920
I managed to get a 16 into his hand.

05:42.922 --> 05:44.622
He's 60 systolic.

05:44.624 --> 05:46.323
His B.P. is crashing fast.

05:46.325 --> 05:48.359
All right, hand me a tourniquet...

05:48.361 --> 05:50.527
and open up the line.

05:50.529 --> 05:53.096
I'm just looking for a vein.

05:53.098 --> 05:54.564
Veins are collapsed.

05:54.566 --> 05:57.334
- Uh, give me a 14 angio...
- Okay.

05:57.336 --> 05:59.268
and set up another line, quickly.

05:59.270 --> 06:00.670
But you said that his veins...

06:00.672 --> 06:01.771
There's one more I can try...

06:01.773 --> 06:04.073
- his jugular.
- Okay.

06:04.075 --> 06:05.641
Let's elevate his legs.

06:05.643 --> 06:08.277
Okay. The blood from his legs
will pool in his upper body

06:08.279 --> 06:09.511
and dilate the vein.

06:09.513 --> 06:11.113
We should be able to get him
some volume fast.

06:11.115 --> 06:12.615
And that will get his B.P. back up.

06:12.617 --> 06:13.816
Exactly.

06:13.818 --> 06:14.884
Okay.

06:20.459 --> 06:24.329
Inserting the angio needle
into his jugular vein.

06:24.331 --> 06:25.664
Okay, we got it.

06:25.666 --> 06:28.533
Line, please.

06:28.535 --> 06:31.870
Okay, I'm opening up the line.

06:37.677 --> 06:40.044
- What happened?
- You just took a little nap.

06:40.046 --> 06:41.679
Now we have to rush you to the hospital.

06:41.681 --> 06:44.181
You're gonna be okay.

06:44.183 --> 06:45.349
Gonna be okay.

06:52.156 --> 06:54.791
Yeah. Hank! Hank, come!

06:54.793 --> 06:56.760
Come on, come on. Hey, guys.

06:56.762 --> 06:59.363
Hey, it's the Mayor of Southampton!

06:59.365 --> 07:01.265
Hi. I've always wanted to meet you, sir.

07:01.267 --> 07:03.167
Pleasure. So, yeah, it's not just me.

07:03.169 --> 07:05.669
That's my brother, Hank Lawson.
I'm Evan. R. Lawson.

07:05.671 --> 07:08.538
That's Divya Katdare,
and together, we are Hankmed.

07:08.540 --> 07:10.207
Hank! So, okay, great.

07:10.209 --> 07:12.242
So, uh, great.
These are my business cards.

07:12.244 --> 07:14.311
Mayor, uh, maybe
you can hand 'em around, bud.

07:14.313 --> 07:15.412
Thanks a lot!

